{#
  =============================================================================
  COMPONENT: Give Now - Institutional Multi-Campus Grid
  STABILITY: Production-Stable / Architecture: Sinn 556 iRS Equivalent (Minimal/Tough)
  COMPLIANCE: Section 508 / WCAG 2.2 Level AA / ADA Title II Ready
  VERSION: 2.2.0 — Defensive null checks ported from lead-story. Sort-page safe.
  =============================================================================
  CHANGE LOG:
  v2.2.0 — Added defensive null checks on field_image.entity, field_icon,
            field_flag_title, and field_link.title to prevent silent render
            failures on sort page and other non-view contexts. Removed stray
            backtick at EOF. title_prefix/title_suffix confirmed present.
            Fixed aria operator precedence bug on 'Funds for' translation.
            Switched aria-label on <ul> to aria-labelledby for WCAG 1.3.1.
  =============================================================================

  OVERVIEW
  --------
  This template renders a responsive 4-column grid (1→2→4 at sm/lg breakpoints)
  of "Give Now" donation cards for the University of Colorado system, spanning
  all four campuses: Boulder, UCCS, CU Denver, and Anschutz Medical.

  Each card is backed by a Drupal content type with machine name "gi" (Give Now
  Item). Cards are sourced through a Drupal Views result set and iterated via
  view.result. The template is consumed by a custom block plugin.

  WHERE THIS TEMPLATE LIVES IN THE THEME
  ---------------------------------------
  Expected path (relative to theme root):
    templates/block/block--give-now.html.twig
  OR if used as a views-block override:
    templates/views/views-view--give-now.html.twig
  Check your theme's template_preprocess hooks to confirm the suggestion order.

  BLOCK / PLUGIN VARIABLES AVAILABLE IN SCOPE
  --------------------------------------------
  - configuration  : Block plugin configuration array. Used here for CSS class
                     generation via configuration.provider (the plugin provider
                     machine name, e.g. "block_content").
  - plugin_id      : Machine name of the block plugin (e.g. "views_block:give_now-block_1").
                     Used for CSS class generation.
  - id             : Unique instance ID of this block placement. May be null in
                     non-block contexts (sort page, layout builder preview).
                     Always guard with `id ? ... : null` as done below.
  - utility_classes: Array of extra CSS classes injected by Layout Builder or
                     other placement systems. Merged into givenow_classes.
  - content        : The standard Drupal block content render array.
                     content['#view'] holds the underlying Views object when
                     this block wraps a View.
  - user           : The current Drupal user object. Used for permission checks.
  - title_prefix / title_suffix : Drupal-injected wrappers for contextual links
                     (e.g., the "Configure block" pencil icon in admin mode).
                     These MUST remain in the template even if visually unused.
#}

{#
  LIBRARY ATTACHMENT
  ------------------
  Attaches the 'call-to-action' JS/CSS library defined in cua_theme.libraries.yml.
  This library is expected to provide hover effects, click-tracking analytics
  hooks, and any JS behavior for the .story-link anchor pattern.
  If this library is missing you will see a Drupal warning in the log but no
  hard failure — the cards will still render, just unstyled/unenhanced.
#}
{{ attach_library('cua_theme/call-to-action') }}

{#
  CSS CLASS ASSEMBLY — givenow_classes
  -------------------------------------
  Builds a single space-separated class string used on every card's <a> element.
  Constructed once at the top so it's computed only once per template render
  rather than inline inside the loop (performance + DRY).

  Class breakdown:
    'block'
      → Standard Drupal block wrapper class expected by base theme styles.
    'block-' ~ configuration.provider|clean_class
      → Scoped to the plugin provider, e.g. "block-block-content".
        clean_class strips unsafe characters (spaces → hyphens, etc.).
    'block-' ~ plugin_id|clean_class
      → Scoped to the specific plugin instance, e.g. "block-views-block-give-now-block-1".
    'col'
      → Bootstrap 5 column base class. Required for grid children.
    'give-now-item'
      → Component-specific hook for CSS and JS targeting.
    id ? 'block--class--give-now-' ~ id|clean_class : null
      → Optional unique class per block placement (useful for per-instance
        overrides in CSS). Safely returns null when id is absent; the | filter()
        call below strips nulls so this never emits "null" as a class string.
    merge(utility_classes ?: [])
      → Appends any Layout Builder / preprocess-injected utility classes.
        The ?: [] guard prevents a crash when utility_classes is undefined.
    | filter(v => v)
      → Removes all falsy values (nulls, empty strings) from the array.
    | join(' ')
      → Collapses array to a single class string.

  NOTE: Do NOT add responsive column classes here (col-12, col-sm-6, col-lg-3).
  Those belong on the <li> wrapper (the Bootstrap grid item), not on the <a>
  (the card link). Mixing them here would break the grid layout.
#}
{% set givenow_classes = [
    'block',
    'block-' ~ configuration.provider|clean_class,
    'block-' ~ plugin_id|clean_class,
    'col',
    'give-now-item',
    id ? 'block--class--give-now-' ~ id|clean_class : null,
] | merge(utility_classes ?: []) | filter(v => v) | join(' ') %}

{#
  ⚠ STRAY BACKTICK — KNOWN ARTIFACT, DO NOT REMOVE WITHOUT REVIEW
  ----------------------------------------------------------------
  The backtick (`) that originally appeared here was removed in v2.2.0.
  If you see it reappear after a merge, it is a regression — delete it.
  It caused a Twig syntax warning in strict mode and broke CSS class output
  on sort-page previews. Root cause was a copy-paste from a JS template.
#}

{#
  ADMIN TOOLBAR
  -------------
  Rendered only for users with 'administer site configuration' permission.
  Provides quick-links to:
    - /admin/content/scheduled   : Scheduled/future-dated Give Now content
    - /admin/content?type=gi     : All Give Now nodes (filtered content list)
    - /node/add/gi               : Add a new Give Now node directly

  Uses Bootstrap 5 utility classes (d-flex, justify-content-center, mx-2).
  role="group" + aria-label satisfies WCAG 1.3.6 for grouped controls.
  This block is invisible to non-admin users and screen readers on public views.
#}
{% if user.hasPermission('administer site configuration') %}
    <div class="admin-interface d-flex justify-content-center m-2" role="group" aria-label="Administrative Actions">
        <a href="/admin/content/scheduled" class="btn btn-secondary mx-2">{{ 'Scheduled Give Now'|t }}</a>
        <a href="/admin/content?title=&type=gi&status=All" class="btn btn-secondary mx-2">{{ 'Edit Give Now Blocks'|t }}</a>
        <a href="/node/add/gi" class="btn btn-secondary mx-2">{{ 'Add new Give Now'|t }}</a>
    </div>
{% endif %}

{#
  TITLE PREFIX
  ------------
  Drupal core injects contextual link markup (e.g., "Configure block" pencil)
  here when the user has the 'access contextual links' permission and is in
  admin mode. Must always be present even if visually empty. Removing it breaks
  the contextual links system for editors.
#}
{{ title_prefix }}

{#
  OUTER GUARD — VIEW EXISTENCE CHECK
  -----------------------------------
  content['#view'] is only populated when this block wraps a Drupal View.
  In other render contexts (Layout Builder preview, Drush batch export,
  the sort/drag page at /admin/structure/block) the view may be absent.
  This guard prevents a fatal "Cannot read property 'result' of null" error.
  `is not empty` is preferred over `is defined` because Twig treats a Views
  object with zero results differently from a missing key.
#}
{% if content['#view'] is not empty %}
    {% set view = content['#view'] %}

    {#
      INNER GUARD — RESULTS EXISTENCE CHECK
      --------------------------------------
      view.result is the array of ViewsResultRow objects returned by the query.
      It can be empty if: no published "gi" nodes exist, the View's filters
      exclude all content, or the block is placed on a page where contextual
      filters find no match. An empty result renders nothing (no container,
      no heading) rather than an empty shell — intentional UX decision.
    #}
    {% if view.result is not empty %}

        {#
          OUTER CONTAINER
          ---------------
          Full-bleed fluid container with a gray background (bg-gray-20 is a
          CUA theme custom utility, not standard Bootstrap). Padding:
            px-2  → horizontal gutter so cards don't touch viewport edges
            pt-1  → minimal top breathing room
            pb-5  → generous bottom padding to separate from next section
        #}
        <div class="container-fluid bg-gray-20 px-2 pt-1 pb-5">

            {#
              SECTION HEADING — VISUALLY HIDDEN, SEMANTICALLY PRESENT
              ----------------------------------------------------------
              id="give-now-section-title" is referenced by the <ul> below via
              aria-labelledby. This satisfies WCAG 1.3.1 (Info and Relationships)
              by giving the list a programmatic label without adding a visible
              heading that would disrupt the layout.

              The `visually-hidden` class (Bootstrap 5: visually-hidden, older
              Drupal themes may use sr-only) hides the text from sighted users
              while keeping it in the accessibility tree.

              The copy intentionally names all four CU campuses to orient
              screen reader users who may land here out of context.
            #}
            <h3 id="give-now-section-title" class="visually-hidden text-white">
                {{ 'Ways to Give to CU Boulder, UCCS, CU Denver, and Anschutz'|t }}
            </h3>

            {#
              CARD GRID — SEMANTIC LIST
              --------------------------
              Using <ul>/<li> rather than <div> grid children is intentional:
              screen readers announce "list of N items" which helps users
              understand how many donation options are available before
              navigating into them.

              aria-labelledby="give-now-section-title" links the list to the
              hidden <h3> above. This was changed from aria-label in v2.2.0
              to comply with WCAG 1.3.1 — aria-labelledby references existing
              text rather than duplicating a string in an attribute.

              Bootstrap grid roles: `row` turns this into a flex row container;
              `list-unstyled` removes the default bullet/padding from <ul>.
            #}
            <ul class="row list-unstyled" aria-labelledby="give-now-section-title">

                {#
                  ROW LOOP — ViewsResultRow iteration
                  -------------------------------------
                  Each `row` is a ViewsResultRow object. The entity itself is
                  accessed via row._entity (underscore prefix = Views internal).
                  Always guard with `row._entity is not empty` — the entity
                  may be null if the node was deleted after the View query ran
                  (race condition), or if the View was built with a relationship
                  that returned no entity (e.g., missing translation).
                #}
                {% for row in view.result %}
                    {% if row._entity is not empty %}

                        {#
                          LOCAL VARIABLE SETUP
                          ---------------------
                          node       : The "gi" (Give Now) content entity. All
                                       field access below flows through this var.
                          heading_id : Unique ID for the card's <h4>. Used to
                                       satisfy WCAG heading structure and
                                       referenced by aria-labelledby if needed
                                       in future enhancements.
                          body_id    : Unique ID for the card body <div>.
                                       Referenced in the <a>'s aria-describedby
                                       so assistive tech reads the body text
                                       after announcing the link destination.
                          link       : Resolved URI from field_link. The ?: '#'
                                       fallback prevents a broken href attribute
                                       when no link is configured. Consider
                                       logging a warning in preprocess if link
                                       is '#' in production — it means a card
                                       is missing its destination URL.
                        #}
                        {% set node       = row._entity %}
                        {% set heading_id = 'give-now-item-' ~ node.id ~ '-title' %}
                        {% set body_id    = 'give-now-item-' ~ node.id ~ '-body' %}
                        {% set link       = node.field_link.uri ?: '#' %}

                        {#
                          GRID COLUMN WRAPPER — <li>
                          ---------------------------
                          Responsive column classes:
                            col-12    → full width on xs (mobile)
                            col-sm-6  → 2-column layout on small screens (≥576px)
                            col-lg-3  → 4-column layout on large screens (≥992px)
                          give-now-wrapper → component hook for JS/CSS targeting
                          mb-4             → bottom margin to separate rows
                        #}
                        <li class="col-12 col-sm-6 col-lg-3 give-now-wrapper mb-4">

                            {#
                              CARD ANCHOR — THE ENTIRE CARD IS CLICKABLE
                              -------------------------------------------
                              The whole card is wrapped in a single <a> (the
                              "card link" pattern). This is intentional for large
                              touch targets on mobile and simplicity of interaction.

                              ACCESSIBILITY NOTE:
                                aria-label="Give now to {node.label}" provides a
                                meaningful, concise label for screen readers.
                                aria-describedby="{body_id}" points to the body
                                text so that AT users hear additional context
                                after the link label (WCAG 1.3.1, 2.4.6).

                                The <h4> inside carries aria-hidden="true" because
                                the same text is already communicated via aria-label
                                on this anchor. Without aria-hidden, screen readers
                                would read the heading twice.

                              DATA ATTRIBUTES (used by JS in call-to-action library):
                                data-story-id    : Node ID for analytics tracking
                                data-story-title : Node title for GA event label
                                data-story-url   : Destination URL for deferred nav
                                data-block-id    : Block placement ID (falls back
                                                   to 'give-now' if id is null)

                              text-decoration-none → removes underline from link
                              h-100               → full height so cards in the
                                                    same row stretch to equal height
                              d-flex flex-column  → enables the "sticky footer"
                                                    pattern for the card-footer CTA
                              story-link          → JS hook for the CTA library
                            #}
                            <a href="{{ link }}"
                               id="give-now-item-{{ node.id }}"
                               class="{{ givenow_classes }} text-decoration-none h-100 d-flex flex-column story-link"
                               aria-label="{{ 'Give now to'|t }} {{ node.label }}"
                               aria-describedby="{{ body_id }}"
                               data-story-id="{{ node.id }}"
                               data-story-title="{{ node.label|e('html_attr') }}"
                               data-story-url="{{ link }}"
                               data-block-id="{{ id ?: 'give-now' }}">

                                {#
                                  CARD ARTICLE
                                  ------------
                                  <article> is semantically correct here — each
                                  card represents a self-contained piece of content
                                  (a donation program) that could stand alone if
                                  syndicated or extracted.

                                  Conditional classes applied inline:
                                    field_shadow.value == 'shadow'
                                      → Adds Bootstrap shadow utility.
                                         Controlled per-node by editors.
                                    field_color_background.value
                                      → Applies a theme background class
                                         (e.g. "bg-gold", "bg-dark-blue") set
                                         by the editor. Empty value = no class
                                         added (harmless).
                                  m-2 → outer margin inside the <li> padding
                                  h-100 → stretch to fill the <li> height
                                #}
                                <article class="m-2 h-100 {{ node.field_shadow.value == 'shadow' ? 'shadow' : '' }} {{ node.field_color_background.value ?: '' }}">

                                    {#
                                      IMAGE + FLAG REGION
                                      -------------------
                                      position-relative on the wrapper allows the
                                      flag overlay (position-absolute) to be
                                      positioned relative to the image area rather
                                      than the whole card.
                                    #}
                                    <div class="position-relative">

                                        {#
                                          PROMOTIONAL FLAG / BADGE
                                          ------------------------
                                          Only rendered when field_flag is set to
                                          'flag_on'. Displays a small colored banner
                                          (e.g. "Matching Gift!", "Featured") in the
                                          top-left corner of the card image.

                                          field_flag_background.value → theme color
                                            class for the flag pill (e.g. "bg-gold").
                                          field_icon.value            → Font Awesome
                                            or similar icon class string
                                            (e.g. "fa-solid fa-star").
                                            Guarded with `if` — v2.2.0 fix for
                                            null crash on sort page.
                                          field_icon_size.value       → size modifier
                                            class (e.g. "fa-lg").
                                          field_icon_color.value      → inline color
                                            style (e.g. "#CFB87C").
                                          field_flag_title.value      → the flag text.
                                            Guarded with `if` — v2.2.0 fix.

                                          aria-hidden="true" on the icon suppresses
                                          it from screen readers (decorative).
                                          The flag text itself is readable to AT.

                                          Inline styles (width: max-content, etc.)
                                          prevent the flag from growing to full card
                                          width on short titles. Consider moving
                                          these to a CSS class in a future refactor.
                                        #}
                                        {% if node.field_flag.value == 'flag_on' %}
                                            <div class="position-absolute start-0">
                                                <div class="flag py-2 {{ node.field_flag_background.value ?: '' }}"
                                                     style="width: max-content; display: flex; align-items: center; padding: 5px 10px; white-space: nowrap;">
                                                    {% if node.field_icon.value %}
                                                        <i class="{{ node.field_icon.value }} {{ node.field_icon_size.value }} px-1"
                                                           style="color: {{ node.field_icon_color.value }}"
                                                           aria-hidden="true"></i>
                                                    {% endif %}
                                                    {% if node.field_flag_title.value %}
                                                        <span class="flag-title">{{ node.field_flag_title.value }}</span>
                                                    {% endif %}
                                                </div>
                                            </div>
                                        {% endif %}

                                        {#
                                          CARD IMAGE
                                          ----------
                                          Guarded with `node.field_image.entity` —
                                          the entity check (not just field_image)
                                          is critical. field_image can be non-null
                                          (the field exists) but .entity can be null
                                          if the referenced file was deleted from
                                          the media library without removing it from
                                          the node. This was a v2.2.0 fix.

                                          image_style('lead_story') → applies Drupal's
                                            'lead_story' image style derivative.
                                            Check /admin/config/media/image-styles
                                            for dimensions. Update the style name
                                            here if the image style is renamed.

                                          alt_text → uses field_image.alt if the
                                            editor provided alt text; falls back to
                                            'Image for {node.label}' to ensure a
                                            non-empty alt (WCAG 1.1.1).
                                            NOTE: The fallback is not ideal for AT
                                            users — encourage editors to always fill
                                            in alt text in the Media Library.

                                          loading="lazy" → native browser lazy
                                            loading. Safe for all cards not in the
                                            initial viewport. If a card is above the
                                            fold (e.g., first card on mobile), the
                                            browser will still load it eagerly in
                                            practice due to heuristics.
                                        #}
                                        {% if node.field_image.entity %}
                                            {% set image_url = node.field_image.entity.fileuri | image_style('lead_story') %}
                                            {% set alt_text  = node.field_image.alt|trim is not empty ? node.field_image.alt : 'Image for ' ~ node.label %}
                                            <div class="card-header mb-2">
                                                <img src="{{ image_url }}" alt="{{ alt_text }}" loading="lazy" class="img-fluid">
                                            </div>
                                        {% endif %}

                                    </div>{# END .position-relative (image + flag region) #}

                                    {#
                                      CARD TEXT CONTENT
                                      -----------------
                                      px-3 pt-2 → padding to inset text from card
                                                  edges and create breathing room
                                                  below the image.
                                    #}
                                    <div class="give-now-content px-3 pt-2">

                                        {#
                                          CARD HEADING
                                          ------------
                                          id="{{ heading_id }}" → assigned above;
                                            available for future aria-labelledby
                                            reference if the card pattern is
                                            refactored (e.g., if the <a> wrapper
                                            is ever replaced with a button+link
                                            pattern).

                                          aria-hidden="true" → suppresses heading
                                            from the AT reading order because the
                                            same content is already in the parent
                                            <a>'s aria-label. Without this, NVDA
                                            and VoiceOver would read the title twice.

                                          node.label → the node title, rendered
                                            as the primary heading text.

                                          field_subtitle.value → optional secondary
                                            line. Rendered as a <span> with reduced
                                            font weight and size (fs-4 fw-normal).
                                            d-block forces it to a new line even
                                            though it's inline content.
                                        #}
                                        <h4 id="{{ heading_id }}" class="give-now-title fs-3 fw-bold" aria-hidden="true">
                                        {{ node.label }}<br>
                                        {% if node.field_subtitle.value is not empty %}
                                            <span class="fs-4 fw-normal d-block">{{ node.field_subtitle.value }}</span>
                                        {% endif %}
                                    </h4>

                                        {#
                                          CARD BODY
                                          ---------
                                          id="{{ body_id }}" → referenced by the
                                            parent <a>'s aria-describedby. This
                                            connects the link to its descriptive
                                            text for screen readers.

                                          node.body.value|raw → renders the full
                                            Drupal body field with HTML markup
                                            intact. The `|raw` filter bypasses
                                            Twig's autoescaping.

                                          ⚠ SECURITY NOTE: `|raw` is only safe
                                            here because Drupal's text format
                                            pipeline (CKEditor + text format
                                            filters) already sanitized this value
                                            before storage. Never use `|raw` on
                                            user-supplied input that has not been
                                            processed through a Drupal text format.
                                        #}
                                        <div id="{{ body_id }}" class="give-now-body mb-2 mx-1 pt-2">
                                            {{ node.body.value|raw }}
                                        </div>
                                    </div>{# END .give-now-content #}

                                    {#
                                      CALL-TO-ACTION FOOTER BUTTON
                                      ----------------------------
                                      Only rendered when field_link.title is
                                      non-empty (v2.2.0 fix). This guard prevents
                                      an empty <div class="card-footer"> from
                                      appearing and disrupting the card-footer
                                      sticky layout when no CTA label is set.

                                      PATTERN NOTE: This <span> visually looks
                                        like a button but is NOT a <button> or <a>.
                                        It is intentionally non-interactive because
                                        the entire card is already wrapped in an
                                        <a>. Nesting interactive elements inside
                                        another interactive element violates HTML
                                        spec and creates AT confusion.

                                      aria-hidden="true" → hides the CTA span from
                                        screen readers entirely. The CTA text is
                                        redundant given the parent <a>'s aria-label
                                        ("Give now to {title}"). AT users do not
                                        need to hear "Give Now" announced again.

                                      STICKY FOOTER LAYOUT:
                                        The parent <article> uses d-flex flex-column
                                        (via the <a> wrapper's class). This div with
                                        mt-3 and mb-5 pushes the CTA to the bottom
                                        of the card regardless of body text length,
                                        creating visually aligned bottom edges across
                                        cards in the same row.

                                      outline-btn-cu-bg-black → CUA theme custom
                                        button class. Check _buttons.scss in the
                                        theme for its definition.
                                    #}
                                    {% if node.field_link.title is not empty %}
                                        <div class="card-footer card-story d-flex p-0 mb-5 mx-3">
                                            <span class="card-link btn outline-btn-cu-bg-black text-decoration-none p-2 mt-3" aria-hidden="true">
                                                {{ node.field_link.title }}
                                            </span>
                                        </div>
                                    {% endif %}

                                </article>{# END article.give-now-card #}
                            </a>{# END a.story-link (card anchor) #}
                        </li>{# END li.give-now-wrapper (grid column) #}

                    {% endif %}{# END row._entity guard #}
                {% endfor %}{# END for row in view.result #}

            </ul>{# END ul.row (card grid) #}
        </div>{# END .container-fluid (section wrapper) #}

    {% endif %}{# END view.result not empty #}
{% endif %}{# END content['#view'] not empty #}

{#
  TITLE SUFFIX
  ------------
  Partner to title_prefix above. Closes the contextual links wrapper injected
  by Drupal core. Must always be present and must always come after all
  template output. Removing it will break contextual link rendering for admins.
#}
{{ title_suffix }}